Special needs trusts
Help ensure the well-being of a loved one with special needs.
A special needs trust, which can be set up by a parent, legal guardian or a court, is designed to provide financial security and long-term care for a beneficiary with mental or physical challenges. Once you set up a special needs trust, it is irrevocable and generally cannot be changed. It protects the assets set aside for the care of your loved one and ensures those assets are managed according to your wishes, even after your death. Furthermore, your beneficiary will retain access to essential governmental benefits, like Supplemental Security Income and Medicaid, and there may be some tax advantages.
At Raymond James Trust, we have the knowledge and expertise to help you with all facets of a special needs trust. From investing and managing the assets to helping you address the specific challenges of your unique case, our experienced professionals are here to support you every step of the way.











